Implicitly differentiating $x^4 + y^4 = 2$ gives

\begin{align*}
4x^3 + 4y^3\cdot y' = 0
\end{align*}

And then we solve for $y'$:

\begin{align*}
4y^3\cdot y' &= -4x^3 \\
y' &= \frac{-x^3}{y^3} 
\end{align*}

